520at%25202%253A22%2520am.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etotal%20solar%20eclipse%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20Monday%20(April%208)%20when%20the%20moon's%20shadow%20will%20fall%20across%20a%20vast%20stretch%20of%20North%20America.%20To%20capture%20this%20rare%20event%2C%20two%20of%20NASA's%C2%A0WB-57%20jet%20planes%2C%20equipped%20with%20special%20instruments%2C%20will%20be%20deployed%20to%20track%20the%20eclipse%20and%20study%20the%20Sun's%20outer%20atmosphere%2C%20known%20as%20the%20corona.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20will%20NASA%20chase%20the%20solar%20eclipse%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENASA%20aims%20to%20uncover%20mysteries%20surrounding%20the%20Sun.%20They%20hope%20to%20gain%20insights%20into%20the%20corona's%20structure%20and%20temperature%2C%20understand%20how%20the%20Sun%20affects%20our%20planet's%20ionosphere%2C%20and%20even%20detect%20hidden%20asteroids%20usually%20obscured%20by%20the%20sun's%20glare.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBharat%20Kunduri%2C%20lead%20researcher%20of%20the%20ionosphere%20measurement%20and%20a%20research%20assistant%20professor%20at%20Virginia%20Tech%20in%20Blacksburg%2C%20Virginia%2C%20said%20in%20a%C2%A0statement%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20eclipse%20basically%20serves%20as%20a%20controlled%20experiment.%20It%20gives%20us%20an%20opportunity%20to%20understand%20how%20changes%20in%20solar%20radiation%20can%20impact%20the%20ionosphere%2C%20which%20can%20in%20turn%20impact%20some%20of%20these%20technologies%20like%20radar%20and%20GPS%20that%20we%20rely%20on%20in%20our%20daily%20lives.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWB-57%20jets%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20WB-57s%20can%20go%20above%20cloud%20cover%20and%20atmospheric%20particles%2C%20reaching%20heights%20of%20up%20to%2050%2C000%20feet%20above%20the%20ground%2C%20which%20allows%20them%20to%20capture%20sharp%20images%20in%20both%20visible%20and%20infrared%20light.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20jets%20will%20be%20timed%20to%20take%20off%20and%20fly%20exactly%20when%20the%20eclipse%20is%20happening.%20They%20will%20fly%20with%20speeds%20reaching%20up%20to%20740%20km%2Fh%2C%20to%20stretch%20out%20the%20time%20we%20can%20see%20the%20eclipse.%20This%20way%2C%20instead%20of%20the%20usual%20length%20of%20around%204%20minutes%20and%2027%20seconds%2C%20they%20will%20extend%20it%20by%20about%2025%25%2C%20giving%20us%20roughly%206%20minutes%20and%2022%20seconds%20of%20totality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EShadia%20Habbal%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hawaii%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CBy%20extending%20the%20duration%20of%20totality%2C%20we're%20increasing%20the%20duration%20of%20how%20much%20data%20we%20can%20acquire.%20This%20light%20is%20our%20best%20probe%20short%20of%20sticking%20a%20thermometer%20in%20the%20corona.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20totality%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EDuring%20a%20total%20solar%20eclipse%2C%20%26quot%3Btotality%26quot%3B%20refers%20to%20the%20brief%20period%20when%20the%20moon%20completely%20covers%20the%20sun%2C%20leaving%20only%20the%20sun's%20outer%20atmosphere%2C%20the%20corona%2C%20visible.%20This%20creates%20a%20dramatic%20spectacle%20where%20the%20sky%20darkens%20significantly%20and%20the%20sun's%20corona%20appears%20as%20a%20glowing%20halo%20around%20the%20darkened%20disk%20of%20the%20Moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20can%20we%20experience%20totality%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ETo%20experience%20totality%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20within%20the%20185%20km-16%2C000%20km%20path%20of%20totality%2C%20which%20falls%20on%20parts%20of%20Mexico%2C%20the%20US%2C%20and%20Canada%20on%20April%208%2C%20according%20to%C2%A0Live%20Science.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712408940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fu0dsm8e_solar-eclipse-unsplash_625x300_06_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhy-nasas-high-speed-jets-will-chase-the-total-solar-eclipse-on-monday-april-8-5387552%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20of%20NASA's%20WB-57%20jet%20planes%20will%20be%20deployed%20to%20chase%20the%20eclipse%20to%20study%20the%20sun's%20outer%20atmosphere%2C%20known%20as%20the%20corona.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhy-nasas-high-speed-jets-will-chase-the-total-solar-eclipse-on-monday-april-8-5387552%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhy-nasas-high-speed-jets-will-chase-the-total-solar-eclipse-on-monday-april-8-5387552%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fwhy-nasas-high-speed-jets-will-chase-the-total-solar-eclipse-on-monday-april-8-5387552%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple's%20had%20a%20pretty%20terrible%20start%20to%20the%20year.%20Here's%20what's%20gone%20wrong%20so%20far.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Apple%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652553726561dd877e75d08a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221331%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETim%20Cook's%20headaches%20keep%20on%20coming.%3Cp%3EAndrej%20Sokolow%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20Apple%20was%20hoping%20that%202024%20would%20start%20smoothly%2C%20it%20was%20very%20much%20out%20of%20luck.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20has%20struggled%20in%20China%2C%20been%20slapped%20with%20a%20massive%20fine%2C%20and%20is%20facing%20a%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMost%20recently%2C%20the%20tech%20giant%20cut%20over%20600%20staff%20aft