tely%201.6%20million%20laying%20hens%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20precaution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcals.cornell.edu%2Fsamuel-david-alcaine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Samuel%20Alcaine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20food%20science%20at%20Cornell%20University%2C%20said%20the%20USDA%20and%20CDC%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbird-flu-avian-influenza-outbreak-us-h5n1-wiping-out-everything-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etracking%20avian%20flu%20for%20a%20while%20now%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20recent%20detection%20of%20it%20in%20cows%20is%20a%20new%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOverall%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20there's%20a%20significantly%20increased%20risk%20to%20the%20US%20consumer%20as%20long%20as%20they're%20already%20following%20the%20basic%20food%20safety%20practices%20that%20we%20should%20be%20following%20at%20home%20anyways%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20he%20shared%20the%20measures%20you%20can%20take%20to%20stay%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMost%20animal%20products%20are%20safe%20to%20eat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20agriculture%20industry%20has%20strict%20protocols%20about%20quarantining%20sick%20animals%20so%20as%20not%20to%20spread%20the%20virus%2C%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F04%2F05%2Fwell%2Feat%2Fbird-flu-dairy-milk-eggs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20most%20commercial%20animal%20products%2C%20such%20as%20milk%2C%20cheese%2C%20and%20liquid%20eggs%20(egg%20yolks)%20go%20through%20a%20pasteurization%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlcaine%20said%20that%20according%20to%20existing%20research%20on%20the%20avian%20flu%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20temperatures%20that%20we%20use%20for%20pasteurization%20are%20more%20than%20adequate%20to%20inactivate%20the%20virus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmbrace%20firm%20egg%20yolks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20extra%20safe%2C%20fully%20cook%20your%20meat%20and%20eggs%2C%20said%20Alcaine.%20Just%20as%20you%20would%20to%20prevent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalmonella-outbreak-linked-to-raw-dough-3-people-in-hospital-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esalmonella%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fe-coli-outbreak-sickening-people-multiple-states-ohio-michigan-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EE.coli%3C%2Fa%3E%20infections%2C%20you%20should%20cook%20meat%20and%20eggs%20at%20hot-enough%20temperatures%20to%20prevent%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Ffoodsafety%2Fcommunication%2Fsalmonella-and-eggs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECDC's%20salmonella%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20cook%20eggs%20until%20both%20the%20egg%20and%20yolk%20are%20firm%2C%20such%20as%20hard-boiled%20or%20scrambled%20eggs.%20(You%20can%20also%20use%20pasteurized%20eggs%20if%20you're%20craving%20them%20poached.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECook%20meat%20to%20the%20right%20internal%20temperature%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20meat%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Ffoodsafety%2Fkeep-food-safe.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20CDC%20recommends%3C%2Fa%3E%20cooking%20ground%20meats%20to%20160%C2%B0F%20and%20poultry%20to%20165%C2%B0F.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Alcaine%20said%20you'll%20want%20to%20be%20wary%20of%20cross-contamination%2C%20such%20as%20keeping%20the%20utensils%20used%20to%20handle%20raw%20meat%20and%20eggs%20away%20from%20cooked%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERaw%20animal%20products%20can%20carry%20bacteria%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20states%20require%20dairy%20products%20to%20be%20pasteurized%2C%20and%20any%20products%20that%20cross%20state%20lines%20must%20be%20pasteurized%20by%20federal%20law%2C%20Dr.%20Sumiko%20Mekaru%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20research%20%26amp%3B%20innovation%20at%20PHC%20Global%2C%20a%20bio%20risk%20threat%20intelligence%20platform%20provider%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FHealth%2Fbird-flu-outbreak-poses-risk-safety-americas-food%2Fstory%3Fid%3D108856122%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20ABC%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworldpopulationreview.com%2Fstate-rankings%2Fraw-milk-legal-states%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20allow%20the%20sale%20of%20raw%20milk%20and%20unpasteurized%20cheese%2C%20which%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2Fmagazine%2F2024%2F03%2F10%2Fthe-alt-right-rebrand-of-raw-milk-00145625%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20in%20popularity%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Alcaine%20said%20that%20there's%20no%20evidence%20%3Cem%3Eyet%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20this%20particular%20virus%20is%20spread%20through%20eating%20raw%20food%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20do%20know%20that%20things%20like%20raw%20milk%20also%20have%20issues%20with%20salmonella%20and%20listeria%20contamination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-raw-unpasteurized-milk-healthy-safe-to-drink-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrinking%20raw%20milk%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20lead%20to%20side%20effects%20like%20vomiting%20and%20diarrhea%2C%20and%20just%20to%20be%20safe%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Femergency.cdc.gov%2Fhan%2F2024%2Fhan00506.asp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECDC%20also%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20abstaining%20in%20light%20of%20this%20recent%20outbreak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbird-flu-eggs-meat-milk-dairy-safety-during-outbreak-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%